        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 22 at 8:12AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 810 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of a snow squall
extending from near Big Sky to near Lima. Movement of this snow
squall was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...This snow squall will produce brief periods of heavy snow,
visibility below one half mile and wind gusts around 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar and observation indicated.

IMPACT...Reduced visibility and snow covered roads will create
difficult travel conditions this morning.

Locations impacted include...
Big Sky, West Yellowstone, Targhee Pass, Raynolds Pass, and Monida
Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>The heavy snowfall will only last about one half hour...consider
delaying travel until the snow squall moves through.</instruction>
